Canto-pop diva Joey Yung and iconic singer-songwriter Anthony Wong not only share the same birthday (June 16), they also shared the stage in their joint concert held in AsiaWorld Arena in November 2008. Decidedly different in their musical styles, these influential singers combined well to give an exciting sound, especially when singing each other's songs, like with Joey's rendition of "Tonight the Stars are Bright", or Anthony's alternative take on "Painful Love". The pair, besides performing their latest numbers individually, also dueted on popular picks like Anthony's "Do You Still Love Me", "Whirlpool", and "Amsterdam", as well as Joey's "On the Treadmill", "My Pride", and "The Splendid Encounter". This 2DVD karaoke release contains a total of 23 songs from the Joey Yung x Anthony Wong concert.

Audio 1 : Dolby Digital Stereo Karaoke
Audio 2 : Dolby Digital 5.1 Concert Vocal
